value: Breeds on the coasts and islands of Bering Sea and contiguous parts of the North Pacific, south to Kodiak Island, Aleutian and Commander Islands, Kamchatka and the Kurile Islands; ranges in summer to Herald and Wrangel Islands and along the north coast of the Chukchi Peninsula. Chiefly resident, but winters south to northern Japan.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Mostly pelagic; nests on talus slopes and beach boulder rubble, occasionally in crevices in cliffs.
